================================================================================
REVIEWED SUMMARY (reviewed — unverified items marked NOT VERIFIED)
================================================================================

C++ emAvlTree.h: low-level intrusive AVL tree via C preprocessor macros.

8 files outside emCore use this type.

emAvlTree is used two ways:
  1. As the engine behind emAvlTreeMap and emAvlTreeSet (wrapper types —
     now ported as emAvlTreeMap.rs and emAvlTreeSet.rs wrapping BTreeMap/BTreeSet)
  2. Directly via raw EM_AVL_* macros in three emCore files

Direct emCore usage and Rust replacements (verified by grep):
  emContext.cpp  — model registry lookup (43 macro invocations)
    -> HashMap in emContext.rs:44
  emPanel.cpp    — child panel lookup by name (17 macro invocations)
    -> HashMap + SlotMap in emPanelTree.rs:245-249
  emListBox.cpp  — item lookup by name (17 macro invocations)
    -> HashMap in emListBox.rs:253

No Rust equivalent exists for:
  emAvlNode / emAvlTree / emAvlIterator — intrusive node struct and
    tree pointer. Rust uses HashMap which manages its own storage.
  EM_AVL_* macros — the entire macro-based insertion/removal/search/
    iteration system. Rust uses HashMap methods directly.
  emAvlCheck() — tree consistency validator. No Rust equivalent found.
  EM_AVL_LOOP / EM_AVL_REV_LOOP — sorted forward/reverse iteration.
    HashMap iteration is unordered.
  EM_AVL_ITER_* — stable iterator that survives mutations.
    HashMap iterators borrow the collection immutably.

Semantic differences (verified):
  Ordering: AVL trees iterate in sorted key order. HashMap does not.
    emContext.cpp uses EM_AVL_LOOP (sorted iteration) in GetListing(),
    GetModelInfo(), SearchUnused(), and SearchGarbage().
    VERIFIED: The only HashMap iteration in emContext.rs is .keys() in
    GetListing() (debug dump) — order-independent. The other EM_AVL_LOOP
    call sites (SearchUnused, SearchGarbage, GetModelInfo) are "find first
    match" or "count all" operations, also order-independent. No Rust code
    depends on HashMap iteration order.

  VERIFIED: All 8 outside-emCore files use only emAvlTreeMap or
    emAvlTreeSet wrappers. None use raw EM_AVL_* macros or emAvlNode.
    Files: emFileManTheme.h/.cpp (emAvlTreeMap<emString,int>),
    emOsmTileCacheCleaner.h (emAvlTreeMap + emAvlTreeSet),
    emStocksPricesFetcher.h/.cpp (emAvlTreeMap), emStocksRec.cpp
    (emAvlTreeSet<int>), emStocksListBox.cpp (emAvlTreeSet<int>),
    emTestContainers.cpp (emAvlTreeMap + emAvlTreeSet).
    emAvlTree is purely an internal implementation detail of emCore.

  VERIFIED: No code outside emCore calls emAvlCheck(). grep for
    "emAvlCheck" in all .h/.cpp files outside emCore returned zero hits.
